    On success, the _nn_ii_cc_ee(3) call returns 0. If it failed, it returns -1 and sets
    errno.

    To check for an error, the application should set errno to zero, then call 
    _nn_ii_cc_ee(3), and if it returns -1, check errno to see if it is non-zero.

